---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
import SectionContext from "../components/SectionContext.astro";

const title = "Oconeco";
const description =
  "OconEco publishes the FAND national balance sheets: 237 countries today, with growing subnational coverage, in an accounting framework that complements GDP.";

const storyArc = [
  {
    heading: "1 · The ancient myth",
    text: "Governance as blind trust in a master pilot.",
  },
  {
    heading: "2 · The American correction",
    text: "Governance as a strict charter where the chart belongs to the sovereign owners.",
  },
  {
    heading: "3 · The modern failure",
    text: "A reductionist instrument panel (GDP) that tracks fuel burn but ignores whether the hull is rotting.",
  },
];

const pathways = [
  {
    href: "/evidence/",
    label: "The Data",
    context:
      "FAND results, navigated by where (geography) and what (balance-sheet component).",
  },
  {
    href: "/framework/",
    label: "What We Measure",
    context:
      "The accounting identity OconEco uses, the scales it operates at, and the vocabulary it introduces.",
  },
  {
    href: "/methodology/",
    label: "Methods",
    context:
      "How OconEco produces each published number, with the audit trail to back it.",
  },
];
---

<SiteLayout title={title} description={description} mainClass="has-hero">
  <section class="hero" slot="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner landing-lead">
      <p class="landing-kicker">Back to the Future &mdash; The Ledger of Consent</p>
      <h1>The Ship of State has a glitch in its instrument panel.</h1>
      <p class="landing-lede">
        Plato thought the passengers were blind cargo and the captain ruled by
        divine right. The American founders disagreed &mdash; they wrote a
        contract that made the passengers the <em>owners</em>, and the
        Enumeration the <em>rudder</em>. FAND restores the rudder.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="hero-video-stub" aria-labelledby="hero-video-heading">
    <h2 id="hero-video-heading" class="visually-hidden">Overview video</h2>
    <div class="hero-video-frame">
      <video class="hero-video" controls preload="metadata" playsinline>
        <source src="/video/FAND_TL1_Overview.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
        <p>
          Your browser can't play HTML5 video.
          <a href="/video/FAND_TL1_Overview.mp4">Download the MP4</a> (17 MB).
        </p>
      </video>
    </div>
    <p class="hero-video-caption">
      A five-minute walkthrough of the FAND framework at the country (TL1) scale.
    </p>
  </section>

  <p class="landing-body-lede">
    A country's wealth is not its cash flow. It is what it <em>owns</em>
    &mdash; produced assets, natural capital, human resources, and substantive
    infrastructure &mdash; what it owes, and the trust infrastructure in
    between. GDP measures earnings; FAND measures ownership. GDP tracks the
    fuel burn. FAND tracks the hull.
  </p>

  <section class="story-cards" aria-label="The story in three acts">
    <ul>
      {storyArc.map((s) => (
        <li class="story-card">
          <h3>{s.heading}</h3>
          <p>{s.text}</p>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="landing-story" aria-label="The Ledger of Consent">
    <p>
      In the founders' late-18th-century usage, "wealth" still carried its
      older sense &mdash; <strong>weal</strong>, the condition of being well,
      the flourishing of the commonweal (Middle English <em>welthe</em>, from
      <em>wele</em>, "well-being"). It was never just a measure of cash flow.
      FAND writes that older sense as <strong>Welth</strong>. The founders were
      <em>founding gardeners</em>: practical vitalists who tracked the unnamed
      miracles of photosynthesis and the rhizosphere because they understood
      that prosperity, like nature, is organic and multi-dimensional.
    </p>
    <p>
      To protect that Welth, the Constitution established a contract between
      the government and the governed. Its steering gear was a radical tool
      &mdash; <strong>the Enumeration</strong> (Article I, &sect;2): a literal
      <em>Ledger of Consent</em>, tying representation and taxation to the
      physical reality of the people. Not ballast to hold the ship in place,
      but the rudder by which the owners steer it.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>In 1890 the tether snapped.</strong> Facing a data backlog, the
      Census adopted Hollerith's punch-card tabulator. Processing became cheap
      overnight &mdash; but the cost of <em>data quality control</em> stayed
      fixed. That asymmetry forced a catastrophic reductionism: the punch card
      couldn't read social trust, institutional reliability, or the organic
      dimensions of Welth, so the state stopped measuring them. Rich
      "chymistry" collapsed into sterile "chemistry" &mdash; and eventually
      into GDP, a metric that counts the liquidation of a forest as growth.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>FAND is the correction.</strong> Agentic AI is the first
      technology that performs <em>contextual</em> quality control at
      near-zero marginal cost. That makes it feasible, for the first time
      since 1890, to rebuild the full multi-dimensional ledger of Welth
      &mdash; Social Infrastructure, Commonwealth, Natural Capital &mdash;
      without it collapsing under its own administrative weight. And because
      contextual measurement is finally cheap, the ledger can be rebuilt the
      way the founding gardeners understood growth &mdash;
      <strong>from the roots up.</strong>
    </p>
  </section>

  <p class="headline-stat">
    <span class="headline-stat-number">237</span>
    <span class="headline-stat-text">
      countries &mdash; measured in one accounting crosstab.
    </span>
  </p>

  <aside class="signal-strip" aria-labelledby="latest-signals-heading">
    <p id="latest-signals-heading" class="signal-strip-heading">
      <strong>Latest signals</strong>
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        A complete national balance sheet &mdash;
        <code>CW = PA + NC + RW; RW = HR + SI</code> &mdash; for 200+
        countries, 1950&ndash;2025.
        <span class="badge badge-prod">Production</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        7,101 administrative units across 237 countries &mdash; and a
        <strong>38&times; measurement asymmetry</strong> between rich-sparse
        and poor-dense regions.
        <span class="badge badge-exp">Experimental</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        A county-level finding: the <em>opportunity</em> to participate tracks
        a community's hidden wealth better than participation itself.
        <span class="badge badge-exp">Experimental</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </aside>

  <section class="pathway-cards" aria-labelledby="choose-depth-heading">
    <h2 id="choose-depth-heading">Choose your depth</h2>
    <ul>
      {pathways.map((p) => (
        <li>
          <a class="pathway-card" href={p.href}>
            <h3>{p.label}</h3>
            <SectionContext>{p.context}</SectionContext>
          </a>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  </section>

  <p class="tools-cta">
    <a href="/tools/"><strong>Enter the Navigation Room &rarr;</strong></a>
    &nbsp;test the live explorers and the worked US ledger.
  </p>
</SiteLayout>
